cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with improving malware detection accuracy. It also involves machine learning and data analysis, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of histogram of gradients (HOG) and convolutional autoencoder suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves proposing a new approach to extract information from icons, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
